  SELECTING "COMMAND PROMPT ONLY" DURING BOOTUP DOESN'T WORK
  
   
   
   After a failed bootup attempt, or if you hit F8 while Win95 is
   starting up, you'll get a menu of bootup options. One of the options
   is Command Prompt Only.
   
   If you select this option, but find that your system still boots into
   Windows, check your AUTOEXEC.BAT file and make sure you don't have a
   command in it that starts Windows. Many people do (I did!). When you
   select Command Prompt Only, Win95 still executes your AUTOEXEC.BAT
   and CONFIG.SYS, but skips the automatic load of Win95 afterward.
   However, if you have a command in AUTOEXEC.BAT that starts Windows,
   it will execute it!
   [6/3/95]
   
   
