  STARTUP FOLDER: WHERE IS THE WINDOWS 95 EQUIVALENT OF THE 'STARTUP' FOLDER?
  
   
   
   If you click the START button, then Settings/Taskbar, you will see
   the panel to modify the taskbar. Select the other tab option at the
   top, then click on 'advanced'. A mini-version of the Explorer will
   pop up, showing the heirarchy of your START menu. One of the items
   listed is 'startup'. This is the equivalent of your Windows 3.1
   startup folder. If you click on that, in the right side of the panel
   you'll see all the things that are automatically run at startup.
   Right click on each item and select 'delete', or drag it to somewhere
   other than the startup area if you want to remove any of these items.
   [6/3/95]
   
   
