  INTERRUPT SETTINGS (IRQS) - WHERE IS A LIST OF MY SETTINGS?
  
   Control Panel/System/Devices, in this area there is an option to
   print a detailed or summary report. The detail report is huge - 18
   pages on my system! The summary report is two pages, and contains a
   list of all the interrupts currently assigned in the system, and what
   they are assigned for. This report also lists DMA channel assignments
   and port addresses.
   
   Another method is to simply right-click on the My Computer icon, and
   select Properties. This will bring up the System control panel.
   Select the Device Manager tab, and double-click on Computer within
   the scrollable window. From here you can view IRQs, DMA channel
   usage, I/O assignments, and Memory settings.
   Thanks to Jeremy Moore for this helpful tip.
   [6/29/95]
   
   
