  ICON PROBLEM: ICONS IN CONTROL PANEL ARE MESSED UP.
  
   There is a known bug where the icon in the Control Panel for Display,
   which normally looks like a monitor, suddenly changes to be something
   else (usually a joystick icon). Just ignore this - Microsoft claims
   it will be corrected in the final shipped version. This affects other
   icons in Control Panel as well, but most usually the Display icon.
   It's also been reported to me that the icon for Explorer sometimes
   changes on its own, too. [6/6/95]
   
   
