  GETTING RID OF THE SHORTCUT ARROWS:
  
   Many people seem to be annoyed by the little arrows that Windows 95
   puts in the lower-left corner of icons that represent shortcuts.
   Well, now you can get rid of them! To do this, use the Registry
   Editor (regedit.exe) to search for these keys:
   
   HKEY_CLASSES_ROOT\lnkfile
   HKEY_CLASSES_ROOT\piffile
   
   Within these keys are strings named "IsShortcut". If you remove (or
   more safely, rename) these to something else, then once you restart
   Windows 95, the arrows will be gone! To restore them, go back into
   regedit and rename the strings back to their previous values.
   Note: As always, editing the Registry can be dangerous, so be
   careful!
   [Thanks to Martin Bean for this tip.]
   
